"How to Make an American Flag The exact proportions of the American Flag have been fixed by executive order; that is to say, by order of the President, as have other features, such as the arrangement and position of the stars.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"The exact size of the flag is variable, though the army has several regulation sizes.",0,0,0,0,0,0
The cut given below shows the dimensions of one of the regulation army flags.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The proportions fixed by executive order on May 26, 1916, are as follows: If the width of the flag be taken as the basis and called 1, then The length will be 1.9, Each stripe will be 1/13 of 1, The blue field will be .76 long and 7/13 of 1 wide.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Other features of the officially designed flag are as follows: The top and bottom stripes are red.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Each State is represented by a five-pointed star, one of whose points shall be directed toward the top of the flag.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Beginning with the upper left-hand corner and reading from left to right the stars indicate the States in order of their ratification of the Constitution and their admission to the Union.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Find your State's star in the following list, and remember its number and line.",1,0,0,0,0,0
