She will take great pains to keep flies out of the kitchen and so will have her windows screened.,1,1,0,1,1,0
"A good kitchen is provided with a sink and if possible with running water; and it must have a good stove, with a place for keeping wood or coal if either is used.",1,0,0,0,0,0
_The Kitchen Floor._ The floor of the kitchen should be made of hard wood.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Maple or hard pine will make a good floor.,0,0,0,0,0,0
A hard-wood floor can be dressed with shellac or with oil.,0,0,0,0,0,0
The wood absorbs this dressing so that water will not soak in.,0,0,0,0,0,0
A floor which has been shellacked should be wiped with warm water.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Not much water will be needed.,0,0,0,0,0,0
