FRUIT--Raw fruit should be carefully washed and prepared in such a way that it can be easily eaten.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Berries may be cooked with no other preparation than washing.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Fruits, such as apples and pears, should be washed, pared, quartered, and cored before cooking.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Any fruit which becomes dark on standing after it is cut may be kept light colored by dropping the pieces into a pan of water until they are ready to be cooked.,1,0,0,0,0,0
If this is done most of the water should be drained off before they are cooked.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Dried fruits, such as prunes, which have a wrinkled skin should be soaked for a short time in cold water before they are washed.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Otherwise it is impossible to get them clean.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"After washing they should be covered with cold water and soaked over night, or until they are plump.",1,0,0,0,0,0
They should be put on to cook in the water in which they are soaked and cooked until tender.,1,0,0,0,0,0
Sugar should then be added if they are not sweet enough.,0,0,0,0,0,0
The most common method of cooking fresh fruit is to boil it gently with just enough water to prevent it from burning.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Sugar should be added just before the cooking is finished, the amount depending on the acidity of the fruit and the taste of the family.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"In sampling food, the cook should remember that the rest of the food is to be eaten by other people.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"She should never taste from the cooking spoon, but should transfer her sample to a tasting spoon which is not returned to the kettle.",1,1,0,1,1,0
"CEREAL--Cereals, such as oatmeal, cornmeal, and cracked wheat, should be cooked in a double boiler.",0,0,0,0,0,0
A double boiler can be improvised by setting a pail or pan into a kettle of boiling water.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Cereals for breakfast may be cooked the day before and reheated in the double boiler, but should not be stirred while reheating.",0,0,0,0,0,0
A tablespoonful or two of cold water on top will prevent a hard skin from forming while standing.,0,0,0,0,0,0
All prepared cereals are better if cooked for a longer time than the package directions indicate.,0,0,0,0,0,0
It is hardly possible to cook any grain too long.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The fireless cooker is especially valuable for cooking cereals, but a longer period of time must be allowed than for cooking in a double boiler.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"A home-made fireless cooker, described in another place, is interesting to make.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Ready-to-serve cereals are very expensive compared with those cooked at home.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Cracked wheat, 1/4 cup to 1 cup water; 3-12 hours.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Rolled oats, 1/2 cup to 1 cup water; 1/2-3 hours Cornmeal, 3 tablespoonfuls to 1 cup water; 1-4 hours.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Use 1/2 teaspoonful of salt to each quart of water.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Have the water boiling rapidly.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Add the cereal gradually.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Let the mixture cook directly over the fire 5 minutes.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Place over boiling water or in the fireless cooker to cook slowly for a long time.,0,0,0,0,0,0
