MEAT--The best way to learn about cuts of meat is to go often to market and talk to the butcher whenever he has a minute to spare.,1,1,1,1,1,1
Some cuts of meat are tough with coarse fibers and much connective tissue.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"They should be ground if, like Hamburg steak, they are to be cooked by a short process, such as broiling.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"If not ground, the tougher meats are usually cooked a long time with water and made into a stew, a pot roast, a meat pie, or a meat loaf.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"These cuts are cheaper, but require more care in preparation than the more expensive cuts.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"Examples are the bottom of the round, the shin, and the flank of beef.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"The more expensive cuts, such as the top of the round, tenderloin and sirloin, are more tender, more delicately flavored, and are used for broiling and roasting.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Some cuts which seem inexpensive really cost more than they appear to because they contain large amounts of bone or waste fat.,1,0,0,0,0,0
The difference between lamb and mutton is a question of the age at which the animal was slaughtered.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Lamb is much more tender than mutton, is more delicately flavored and more expensive.",0,0,0,0,0,0
There is a similar difference between chicken and fowl.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Fowl is much tougher than chicken and requires careful and long cooking to make it tender.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"_Pan Broiled Hamburg Steak_--Hamburg steak may be bought already ground at the butcher's, or one of the cheap cuts of beef, such as bottom of the round or shin, may be bought and ground at home.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Many people like a little salt pork or onion ground with the meat.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Make the meat into small, flat cakes and cook in a smoking hot frying pan which has been thoroughly rubbed over with a piece of fat.",0,0,0,0,0,0
When one side is seared over nicely turn the cakes (a griddle cake turner or spatula is helpful) and broil on the other side.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Place on a hot platter, sprinkle with salt and pepper, dot with bits of butter and garnish with a little parsley or watercress.",0,0,0,0,0,0
