"Wipe and trim the steak, place in a smoking hot frying pan and sear both sides.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Reduce the heat and turn the steak occasionally (about every 2 minutes) until it is cooked, allowing 8 minutes for a rare steak, 10 minutes for medium cooked steak, and 12 minutes for well done steak, for a steak 1 inch thick.",1,0,0,0,0,0
Avoid puncturing the meat with a fork while cooking.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Many people prefer to broil a steak on a broiler.,0,0,0,0,0,0
This is practical with gas or electricity or over a wood or coal fire which is reduced to clear coals without smoke or flame.,0,0,0,0,0,0
It is very difficult indeed to cook Hamburg steak on a broiler.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Lamb chops may be broiled in either way.,0,0,0,0,0,0
