_Bones_--Great care must be taken in handling a baby.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Its bones are soft and easily injured, and for this reason a baby should not be handled more than necessary.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"When very young its entire spine should be supported, and no undue pressure made upon the chest, as often happens if the baby is grasped under the arms.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"In lifting a young baby from its bed, the right hand should grasp the clothing below the feet, and the left hand should be slipped beneath the infant's body to its head.",1,0,0,0,0,0
It is then raised upon the left arm.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"An older child should be lifted by placing the hands under the child's arms, and never by the wrists.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"If children are jerked or lifted by the arms, serious injury may be done to the bones.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"The bones, when a child is growing, are partly composed of soft tissue which is easily destroyed, and further growth is prevented.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Many children are brought to the hospitals with injuries done to their arms from being jerked across the street.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Do not let a child walk too soon, especially a heavy child.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Bow legs and knock knees come from standing and walking when the bones are soft.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"_Exercise_--At least twice a day an infant should be allowed for fifteen or twenty minutes the free use of its limbs by permitting it to lie upon a bed in a warm room, with all clothing except the shirt and diaper removed.",1,0,0,0,0,0
In cold weather leave on the stockings.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Later, when in short clothes, the baby may be put upon a thick blanket or quilt, laid upon the floor, and be allowed to tumble at will.",0,0,0,0,0,0
_Rest_--Healthy children never sleep too much.,0,0,0,0,0,0
A new born baby should sleep nine-tenths of the day.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"A child should have a nap during the day until four years old, and, if possible, until seven or eight years old.",0,0,0,0,0,0
It should go to bed before six.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"It should have a crib or bed to itself, placed where it will have fresh air, but protected from draughts, and its eyes protected from direct rays of light.",1,0,0,0,0,0
