"Pulse The pulse may be counted on the thumb side of the inside of the wrist, at the temples, the ankles, and other parts of the body where the arteries are near the surface.",0,0,0,0,0,0
The pulse shows the number of times per minute which the heart beats or pumps.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"A normal pulse rate for a man is around 72, for a woman 80, for a child 90, and for a baby 100 beats.",0,0,0,0,0,0
A very rapid or a very slow pulse shows that there is something wrong that should be reported.,0,0,0,0,0,0
It takes a good deal of practice to learn to count the pulse.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Place two or three fingers on the beating artery, just touching firmly enough to feel the beats, and count for a half minute, then multiply by two to find the number of beats per minute.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Be sure that the patient's hand is in a comfortable position while counting.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Respiration Respiration is another word for breathing.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"An average normal person when sitting or lying still, breathes from twelve to twenty times per minute, and when moving about 24 times.",0,0,0,0,0,0
We all know that quick moving makes quick breathing.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Respiration above 40 or below 8 is a danger sign.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"If the respiration is very fast, or difficult, or wheezy, or in any way very unusual, we can tell it at a glance.",1,0,0,0,0,0
People who are breathing hard are frequently relieved by being propped up in bed.,0,0,0,0,0,0
_To count the respiration._ It is better to do this without the person's knowledge.,0,0,0,0,0,0
It may be counted by watching the rise and fall of the chest or of the shoulders.,0,0,0,0,0,0
