SECTION XII SETTING-UP EXERCISES FOR GIRL SCOUTS Our bodies are like machines that need frequent oiling and testing to see that all parts are working right.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Or they are like instruments that must be tuned before they are played.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"If this is not done, the machinery gets rusty and clogged, or the instrument gets out of tune and makes horrid noises.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"That is the way it is with our bodies; our muscles and joints should be bent and stretched every day to take the kinks out, and keep them strong and flexible.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"The best way is to tune up every morning for just a few minutes before you put on your clothes, and then again at night to rest the tired parts and exercise the parts that have not been used, so you can even things up.",0,0,0,0,0,0
=The Right Position= First of all try to stand in the right position.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"[Illustration] Stand with the feet side by side, a few inches apart and pointed straight ahead.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Many people think you should turn out your toes because they think it looks better.,1,0,0,0,0,0
This is not natural.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"If you stand on a step with one foot even with the edge, and let the other foot hang over the step below, it will hang parallel with the foot you are standing on.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"That is the way it is meant to go, and people who turn out their toes do so much walking sideways that they have to travel much farther than if they kept their feet pointed in the direction they want to go.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"[Illustration] Then your legs should come up straight from your ankles; don't stand either on your heels or your toes, but right over the highest part of the arch, which is the strongest part, and best fitted to bear your weight when you are standing still, and brings your hips up to just the right place to hold your body.",1,0,0,0,0,0
*       *       *       *       * In the lower part of your body are some big heavy bones shaped somewhat like a bowl.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"This bowl is balanced on the top of your legs, and holds most of your organs.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"If this bowl is balanced just right, the organs remain in place, the way they are meant to be, but if it is not balanced right, the contents are tipped so that they would come tumbling out if the muscles intended for other work did not hold them in.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"This is hard on these muscles which have their own work to do, and if they are used to hold up things that should keep their own balance, sooner or later they give way, and there is a sad accident, or a general slump.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"Then instead of saying, That foolish person always stood in the wrong position and of course her insides got out of place, we say, Poor dear so-and-so has given out from overwork and has acute indigestion, or a 'floating kidney,' or 'a bad liver.'",0,0,0,0,0,0
How could it have happened?,0,0,0,0,0,0
If your underpinning is all right it is not difficult to be straight above.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Let your shoulders hang easily in a straight line under your ears, in the position they will naturally take if from side stretch (fig.",1,0,0,0,0,0
3) the arms drop easily to the side.,0,0,0,0,0,0
_Don't arch your chest and throw your shoulders back!_ This is not a slump and does not mean to let your back bow out.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"If your shoulders are easy you can straighten your back and your head will balance itself, and there you are: a straight upstanding Scout, ready for what comes next.",1,0,0,0,0,0
Remember: a) Feet pointing straight ahead.,0,0,0,0,0,0
b) Body balanced on legs coming up straight from           ankles.,0,0,0,0,0,0
