"EDIBLE WILD PLANTS No one truly knows the woods until he can find with certainty a number of wild plants that furnish good food for man in the season when food is scarce; that is, in the winter or early spring.",1,1,1,1,1,1
"During summer and autumn there is always an abundance of familiar nuts and berries, so that we may rule them out, and seek only for edible plants and roots that are available when nuts and berries are not.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"_Rock Tripe._ The most wonderful of all is probably the greenish-black rock tripe, found on the bleakest, highest rocks in the northern parts of this continent.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"There is a wonderful display of it on the cliffs about Mohonk Lake, in the Catskills.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"Richardson and Franklin, the great northern explorers, lived on it for months.",0,0,0,0,0,0
It must be very carefully cooked or it produces cramps.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"First gather and wash it as clear as possible of sand and grit, washing it again and again, snipping off the gritty parts of the roots where it held onto the mother rock.",1,0,0,0,0,0
Then roast it slowly in a pan till dry and crisp.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Next boil it for one hour and serve it either hot or cold.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"It looks like thick gumbo soup with short, thick pieces of black and green leaves in it.",1,0,0,0,0,0
It tastes a little like tapioca with a slight flavoring of licorice.,0,0,0,0,0,0
On some it acts as a purge.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"_Basswood Browse or Buds._ As a child I ate these raw in quantities, as did also most of my young friends, but they will be found the better for cooking.",1,0,0,0,0,0
