Signal by Shots The old buffalo hunters had an established signal that is yet used by the mountain guides.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"It is as follows: Two shots in rapid succession, an interval of five seconds by the watch, then one shot; this means, where are you?",0,0,0,0,0,0
The answer given at once and exactly the same means Here I am; what do you want?,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The reply to this may be one shot, which means, All right; I only wanted to know where you were.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"But if the reply repeats the first it means, I am in serious trouble; come as fast as you can.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Totems in Town A totem is an emblem of a man, a group of men, or an idea.",0,0,0,0,0,0
It has no reference to words or letters.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Before men knew how to write they needed marks to indicate ownership.,1,0,0,0,0,0
This mark must be simple and legible and was chosen because of something connected with the owner or his family.,1,1,1,1,1,1
Later some of the trades adopted a symbol; for instance the barbers in the early days were blood letters and were closely associated with the medical profession.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Their totem indicate their business and we have the red and white barber pole of today.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"It was among the Indians along the West coast of America that the science and art of totems reached its highest development, though they have a world-wide usage and go back in history to the earliest times.",1,0,0,0,0,0
Out of this use of totems as owner marks and signs grew the whole science of heraldry and national flags.,0,0,0,0,0,0
