_Water_--Be particularly careful about the purity of your water supply.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"You come, let us say, to a mountain brook, that issues from thick forest.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"It ripples over clean rocks, it bubbles with air, it is clear as crystal and cool to your thirsty throat.",1,0,0,0,0,0
'Surely that is good water.',0,0,0,0,0,0
But do you know where it comes from?,0,0,0,0,0,0
Every mountain cabin is built close to a spring-branch.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Somewhere up that branch there may be a clearing; in that clearing, a house; in that house, a case of dysentery or typhoid fever.",1,0,0,0,0,0
I have known several cases of infection from just such a source.,0,0,0,0,0,0
It is not true that running water purifies itself.,0,0,0,0,0,0
