"Indeed, a meal may be cooked without any equipment whatever other than a knife which every Scout should be provided with.",0,0,0,0,0,0
_Improvised Grate_--A few sticks 1/2 inch in diameter laid about 2 inches apart and about 2 inches above the coals form a good enough broiler.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Steak and chops cook perfectly well if laid right on the coals.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Cooking kits allow for more variety, as they provide a frying pan, in which bacon and potatoes can be cooked, and a small pail for boiling water.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"It is convenient for each Scout to carry her own cup, knife, fork and spoon.",0,0,0,0,0,0
The cooking kit and supplies can then be divided among the party.,0,0,0,0,0,0
At a permanent camp a frying board is a great convenience.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"It is simply a flat, smooth board with a pointed end which can be driven into the ground.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Fish, meat, game and Injun bread can be cooked on this board better than in any other way, as the food receives the heat without becoming charred, and is much more wholesome than when fried in a pan.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"As long as the board is to windward of the flame, a constant heat is maintained without smoke.",0,0,0,0,0,0
A small fire will cook a very large fish in a short time.,0,0,0,0,0,0
