"Provisions When a party camps where fresh meat and farm products can be procured as they are wanted, its provisioning is chiefly a matter of taste, and calls for no special comment here.",1,0,0,0,0,0
But to have good meals in the wilderness is a different matter.,0,0,0,0,0,0
A man will eat five or six pounds a day of fresh food.,0,0,0,0,0,0
That is a heavy load on the trail.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"And fresh meat, dairy products, fruit and vegetables are generally too bulky, too perishable.",0,0,0,0,0,0
So it is up to the woodsman to learn how to get the most nourishment out of the least weight and bulk in materials that 'keep' well.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Light outfitting, as regards food, is mainly a question of _how much water_ we are willing to carry in our rations.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"For instance, canned peaches are 88 per cent.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Can one afford to carry so much water from home when there is plenty of it at camp?,1,0,0,0,0,0
"The following table is suggestive:           More than 3/4 water           Fresh milk, fruit, vegetables (except potatoes).",0,0,0,0,0,0
