"_Dehydrated Vegetables_--Much of the flavor of fresh vegetables is lost when the juice is expressed or evaporated, but all of their nutriment is retained and enough of the flavor for them to serve as fair substitutes when fresh vegetables cannot be carried.",1,0,0,0,0,0
They help out a camp stew and may even be served as side dishes if one has butter and milk to season them.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Generally they require soaking (which can be done over night); then they are to be boiled slowly until tender, taking about as much time as fresh vegetables.",1,0,0,0,0,0
If cooking is hurried they will be woody and tasteless.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Dehydrated vegetables are very portable, keep in any climate, and it is well to carry some on trips far from civilization.",0,0,0,0,0,0
_Canned Vegetables_--In our table of food values it will be noticed that the least nourishing article for its weight and bulk is a can of tomatoes.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Yet these 'air-tights' are great favorites with outdoors men, especially in the West and South, where frequently they are eaten raw out of the can.",0,0,0,0,0,0
