Camp Cooking Meat and fish are easy to cook and require few utensils.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Steaks or chops require from four to twelve minutes to broil rare over a good bed of live coals, depending on the thickness of the meat.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Place either directly on the coals in wire broiler and raise only an inch or two above the fire.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Turn after about 1-1/2 minutes, and afterward turn a little oftener to prevent burning.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Chicken or duck of broiling size takes about 20 minutes to broil and requires very particular care in frequent turning to prevent burning.,0,0,0,0,0,0
Turn about every 1/2 minute.,0,0,0,0,0,0
As portions of the skin show signs of getting too brown baste them with a few drops of hot water from a large spoon.,1,0,0,0,0,0
This also tends to keep them moist.,0,0,0,0,0,0
The poultry may be cooked by propping the wire broiler upright six to nine inches from a blazing fire.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Often the poultry is started this way and finished over the coals, as this saves considerable time in waiting for the fire to burn down.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"The chicken or duck may be hung close to the fire by a wire from a slanting pole, revolving frequently.",0,0,0,0,0,0
An hour is required to roast poultry.,0,0,0,0,0,0
