"Reptiles Reptiles include Alligators, Crocodiles, Turtles, Lizards and Snakes.",0,0,0,0,0,0
It is commonly said that reptiles are cold-blooded.,0,0,0,0,0,0
This means that the temperature of their blood varies and is the same as the surrounding medium.,0,0,0,0,0,0
The temperature of an Alligator that has been floating with its nose out of the water is the same as the surrounding water.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The temperature of a turtle in the winter time is the same as the mud in which it is buried, while in the summer time it is much higher.",1,0,0,0,0,0
What is true of the reptiles in respect to temperature is also true of Amphibians and Fishes.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"However, this is not true of Birds and Mammals, for these have a uniform temperature so high that they are called warm-blooded.",1,0,0,0,0,0
