"(2) The Preparation of the Seed Bed The first thing to do, after having determined the location of your garden, is to measure your bed.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"If you have a single bed, one twelve feet long by six feet wide is enough to start with.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"I should prefer, however, to have two beds, each three feet wide by twelve feet long with a narrow path between, say, twelve inches.",0,0,0,0,0,0
